The paper deals with the combinatorial and topological structure of tilings, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of Cantor-Bendixson rank suggests a connection to general topology (cs.CG), while the investigation of periodic tilings and their properties may fall under graph theory (cs.GT). The introduction of a pattern preorder and the study of countable and uncountable cases may also involve logic and set theory (cs.LO). Finally, the analysis of tilings as a system may have applications in control theory and systems engineering (cs.SY).
